<collectingCountry box="[500,588,475,501]" name="Taiwan" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
by its elongate and slender body with very finely punctate dorsal surface and incomplete ocular sulcus. See also the subsequent key to the Taiwanese species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MERKL et MASUMOTO" authorityYear="2007" box="[693,923,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Paramisolampidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[693,923,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Paramisolampidius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
